			interface Data {
				x: number
			}
			let d:Data = <any> this.$route.params.data

### What is expected?
Change Location.params and Route.params to any 

### What is actually happening?
1. Location.params: 
When I use this.$router.push({params: {data:{}}}) to pass object data between pages, TS will report an error. Currently, every push writes any to solve the problem.

2. Route.params:
When I use this.$route.params.data to get the data passed by other pages, and the assigned variable has a custom type, TS will report an error, which can only be solved by <any>.

